“ ‘I rejoice with the greatest joy in whatever merit has arisen from the generosity of beings in the ten directions,
                        from their good conduct, and from the merit that has arisen from their meditation.  I rejoice in that merit with a joy that is sublime, preeminent, superior, complete,
                        perfect, excellent, the highest, unsurpassable, superlative, unequaled, and that has no equal.
